Credit Risk & Liquidity Risk: It states there was no significant credit risk for 2023 as company funds were placed only in well-rated banks. Liquidity management included monitoring projected and actual cash flows and maturity dates of assets/liabilities. 


Operational Risks: These included air quality and noise during construction, mitigated by measures like protective equipment, watering of dusty areas near communities, and off-peak transport. 
Scribd

Risks related to local employment, public perception, environmental aesthetics, and fire hazards were managed through local hiring, community engagement, waste management, and emergency preparedness coordination.
